<HL>
   Aerovox Inc. Stake
   Of 6.7% Is Acquired
   By Texas Art Group
</HL>
<DATE>
06/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7F
</SO>
<CO>
   ARVX
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- A group including Houston-based Texas Art
Supply Co. said it acquired a 6.7% stake in Aerovox Inc., New
Bedford, Mass., for investment purposes.
   The group, in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing,
said it holds a total of 340,234 Aerovox common shares, all
but 134 shares of which were bought in the open market
between April 12 and June 1 at $3.50 to $4.50 a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The group also includes members of the Adler family and
the Adler Foundation of Houston. Louis K. Adler is president
of Texas Art Supply.
   The group said it acquired its Aerovox stock as an
investment and doesn't currently plan to seek control of the
company or to acquire a substantial amount of shares. Mr.
Adler, however, may seek board representation, the filing
said.
</TEXT>
